y elements affecting black employment and advancement? What real effect has court action had on the problem of assigning blacks their rightful place in the seniority order?This study is based upon individual reports on specific industries first published in the Racial Policies of American Industry series. New, updated material has been added, and the first chapter is designed to give an overview of the several industries discussed. A final chapter compares and contrasts the situations in the six industries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAfrican AmericansxEmployment. 0aDiscrimination in employmentzUnited States. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Labor.2bisacsh  aBusiness.  aEconomics.1 aDenison, Marjorie C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Carl B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNorthrup, Herbert R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuay, William Howard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRisher, Howard W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRowan, Richard L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRowan, Richard L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Press Package Archive 1898-1999z978311044252640uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978151282110940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781512821109423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781512821109.jpg  a978-3-11-044252-6  University of Pennsylvania Press Package Archive 1898-1999c1898d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMA